{"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"centerOffset","symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","title":"MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"title":"centerOffset","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"}}}